                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Dec. 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#47;88<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>During the month of<lb/> November the Seminary classes<lb/> continued the subjects fixed upon<lb/> for this year.  The Preparatory<lb/> Department continued the reading<lb/> of Genesis with &#91;Hebrew&#93; to the end of<lb/> Cap. XXV&#44; read Psalms LII &#38; LIII&#44; Joshua<lb/> at sight to the end of Cap. VIII&#44; con&#45;<lb/>&#45;tinued the history of the division of<lb/> the land and the grammar through<lb/> the pronouns and the rudiments of<lb/> the verb.  The Junior Department<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>continued the reading of Isaiah to<lb/> Cap. V&#44; the grammar through verbs<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; and the history to the end of<lb/> the period of Ezra and Nehemiah.<lb/>  In accordance with the agreement<lb/> made during your recent presence<lb/> in New York&#44; the Junior Department<lb/> has been instructed to prepare<lb/> an essay in English and one in<lb/> Hebrew to be ready at the end of<lb/> January.  For the English essay<lb/> I have given two subjects of which<lb/> the students are at liberty to choose<lb/> whichever one they prefer.  The first<lb/> is &#34;The importance of Grammar<lb/> for the correct study of the Hebrew<lb/> language and Jewish literature&#44;&#34; the<lb/></p> 
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>second &#34;The period of Ezra and Nehemi&#45;<lb/>&#45;ah in its relation to the history of<lb/> Judaism.&#34;  The Hebrew essay is pro&#45;<lb/>&#45;posed  by Dr. Lieberman and is on<lb/> the thirteen hermeneutical rules<lb/> of R. Ishmael.<lb/></p>
            <p>The essays are to be passed on by<lb/> the faculty.<lb/></p>
            <p>This comprises everything of importance<lb/> during the month of November.<lb/>  I remain<lb/> very respectfully<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>From<lb/>
                329 E. 51<hi rend="sup">st</hi> St<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">N. Y</hi><lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 N. 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
            </body>
